data.title: Rosalind Chao (AKA Keiko) was on Grey's Anatomy Last Night
data.meta_description: For those of you that didn't catch Grey's Anatomy last night, Rosalind Chao (AKA Keiko) did a guest spot on the show as a patient.  She didn't have many...
data.text:
For those of you that didn't catch Grey's Anatomy last night, Rosalind Chao (AKA Keiko) did a guest spot on the show as a patient. She didn't have many lines... as she was playing a patient that was waiting for Dr. Sloan to construct her a new voice box.

And of course Mary McDonnell of nuBSG was on the show again!

Speaking of Rosalind, many may not be aware that she married Klinger on M*A*S*H, which is also one of my favorite all time TV series.

Resistance is Futile

Speaking of Rosalind, many may not be aware that she married Klinger on M*A*S*H, which is also one of my favorite all time TV series.

Resistance is Futile

Actually, Rosalind Chao's character on M*A*S*H married Corporal Klinger, and not the actual actor who played him.

I also recently watched a documentary called Nanking in which Ms. Chao was one of the actresses who dramatized the horrific invasion of the Japanese army into Nanking China in 1937.

^Actually, Klinger was a Sergeant at the time.

Anyway, I missed her on Grey's Anatomy, but yeah I did notice her on M*A*S*H not too long ago

When I submitted my post I was thinking that some people may think that she had married Jamie Farr, who played Maxwell Klinger. I meant to clarify it, but never got around to it. Thanks for doing it for me

Am I the only one who was disappointed when Sloan successfully restored her voice?

I was holding out hope that Keiko would finally shut the hell up...
